SCRIPT 

SAD INTRO: 

(INSERT ART) GRANDPA BEE: A long time ago, when all was well, the bees were happy, the honey was plentiful, and the children were frolicking. But one faithful day, horror struck. The wasp colony attacked. Without warning, they stripped us of our home. Burning our hives to the ground. (INSERT ART)


All was lost in the fire….. Including my beloved grobby poo. She was the light of my life, but now, she burns. I live with my agony every day. (INSERT ART)

(INSERT ART) Ehem... anyway. Legend has it that beyond the great vast land lies one last hive. It is up to you to find it and continue the bee-autiful life. Collect honey along the way, give it to the hive as an offering and a means of aid from the wasp attack. Honey is at an all-time low thanks to the wasps. The bees are too scared to leave their hives. 

Here, a sacred jar to collect honey. But beware… the wasps are still buzzing around. 

(SLOW FADE TO LEVEL ONE)


LEVEL ONE: “THE BACKYARD BEE”

(BEFORE LEVEL STARTS)
GRANDPA BEE: BEE-CAREFUL… you take damage from wasps. Use WASD to fly up and down. To collect honey, fly near it. But watch out, wasps like honey too…

ENDING OF LEVEL ONE: 
GRANDPA BEE: I cannot BEE-lieve you managed to collect enough pollen. Grandpa is so proud. But not proud enough. You still have a long way to go before you reach the hive. Dont tell me you thought THAT was enough honey to give to LAST BEE COLONY.

BACKPACK BEE: HOWDY DOO! I thought I was the last bee! 

GRANDPA BEE: jumpscare… what's with the pouch?

BILL THE BACKPACK BEE: I use it to store loads of pollen and my backpack transforms it into honey!

GRANDPA BEE: Hmm, that definitely makes sense.  you seem to know what you're doing.. You two should join teams. With this “backpack bee,” you should be able to collect WAY more honey now! 

( POP UP ON SCREEN) “YOU'VE UNLOCKED BACKPACK BEE”
He can carry pollen! What else did you expect?
BackPack Bee can help you carry more pollen! With his magic, funky backpack, he can help turn pollen into honey.

