(ALL BEES START GOING ACROSS THE SCREEN TO THE NEW HIVE, PETER STAYS)

Grandpa Bee: You coming?

Peter: You go on without me, there's still work left undone

ALL BEES (besides grandpa): YOU CAN TALK?

Peter: We may have gathered honey to make honeycomb to build the hives, but I feel like something's still missing.

Grandpa: Pollen: missing you, say..

Peter: Yes..

BOUGIE BEE: Well, we could use some pollen, those wasps really wiped out our pollen collectors..

Peter: I can help.

BOUGIE BEE: That would be quite helpful. But you've already done so much.

Peter: If there's more work to be done. Then im the bee to do it

BOUGIE BEE: Im sorry, I dont believe you ever told me your name

Peter: It's Peter, Peter the Pollen Collector

